\begin{matrix}
&amp; \text{Dynamic Station} &amp; \text{Rate of Change} \\
\hline
\text{Heat} &amp; \text{Diffuses} &amp; \text{Rate of Change of
TEMPERATURE} \\
\hline
\text{Wave} &amp; \text{Propagates} &amp; \text{Rate of Change of ENERGY
OF WAVE} \\
\hline
\text{Population} &amp; \text{Grows} &amp; \text{Rate of Change of
POPULATION} \\
\hline
\text{Object} &amp;  \text{Moves} &amp; \text{Rate of Change of
DISPLACEMENT} \\
\end{matrix}
}\]</span></p>
</section>
<section id="definition" class="slide level2">
<h2>Definition</h2>
<p><span class="math display">\[F(x , y, x&#39;, y&#39;, x&#39;&#39;,
y&#39;&#39;, \ldots , x^n, y^n) = 0\]</span></p>
<p><em>Example</em>:</p>
<p><span class="math display">\[y&#39;&#39; - 2xy&#39; + y =
x^2\]</span></p>
</section>
<section id="example-in-physics" class="slide level2">
<h2>Example in Physics</h2>
<p><span class="math display">\[\vec{F}_{net}=k\vec{v}(t)\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[\bigtriangleup\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[|\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[\bigcirc\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[|\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[\bigtriangledown\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[\vec{F}_{net}=- m\vec{g}\]</span> <span
class="math display">\[\]</span></p>
<p><span class="math display">\[\vec{F}_{net}=m \vec{a}\]</span></p>
<p><span class="math display">\[k\vec{v}(t) - m\vec{g} = m
\vec{a}\]</span></p>
<p><span class="math display">\[k {\dot{y}}(t) - m {\ddot{y}}(t) -
m\vec{g} = 0\]</span></p>
</section></section>
<section>
<section id="classification" class="title-slide slide level1">
<h1>Classification</h1>

</section>
<section id="section-1" class="slide level2">
<h2></h2>
<p><span class="math display">\[{
\begin{matrix}
\text{Number of independent variables} &amp; \text{Short Name} &amp;
\text{Name} \\
\hline
\text{1} &amp; \text{ODE} &amp; \text{Ordinary Differential Equation} \\
\text{more than 1} &amp; \text{PDE} &amp; \text{Partial Differential E-quation} \\
\end{matrix}
}\]</span></p>
</section>
<section id="section-2" class="slide level2">
<h2></h2>
<p><span class="math display">\[{
\begin{matrix}
\text{Linear} &amp; \text{Non Linear} \\
\hline
\text{in the form of: } \sum\limits_{n=0}^{N} a_n y^n \text{    } &amp;
\text{    } \text{NOT in the form of: } \sum\limits_{n=0}^{N} a_n y^n \\
\end{matrix}
}\]</span></p>
</section>
<section id="section-3" class="slide level2">
<h2></h2>
<p>If a differential equation is homogeneous in the unknown functions
and its derivatives then it is said to be homogeneous</p>
<p><span class="math display">\[\begin{matrix}
y&#39;+y=x &amp; \text{nonhomogeneous} \\
xy&#39;+y=0 &amp; \text{homogeneous} \\
sin(\ddot{y})-cos(y)=x^2 &amp; \text{nonhomogeneous} \\
\end{matrix}\]</span></p>
</section></section>
